main event: Two bright lights were observed in the sky over Duluth, Minnesota, on September 9, 1960.
interesting points: The lights were large and very bright, flashing red, blue, and yellow which appeared to be navigational lights., The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes., The lights disappeared suddenly in a south direction., There were no pronounced halos or tails observed around the lights., The observation was made using ground-radar from military personnel.
witness description: Military personnel at Duluth Air Base observed the lights.
